01:39:17.203 --> 01:39:23.733
<i>But the bitter truth we critics must face</i>
<i>is that in the grand scheme of things,</i>

01:39:23.843 --> 01:39:27.836
<i>the average piece of junk</i>
<i>is probably more meaningful</i>

01:39:27.947 --> 01:39:31.212
<i>than our criticism designating it so.</i>

01:39:31.584 --> 01:39:35.714
<i>But there are times</i>
<i>when a critic truly risks something</i>

01:39:35.821 --> 01:39:40.121
<i>and that is in the discovery</i>
<i>and defense of the new.</i>

01:39:40.226 --> 01:39:44.822
<i>The world is often unkind</i>
<i>to new talent, new creations.</i>

01:39:45.030 --> 01:39:47.498
<i>The new needs friends.</i>

01:39:47.800 --> 01:39:51.327
<i>Last night,</i>
<i>I experienced something new,</i>

01:39:51.537 --> 01:39:56.497
<i>an extraordinary meal</i>
<i>from a singularly unexpected source.</i>

01:39:56.709 --> 01:39:59.337
<i>To say that both the meal</i>
<i>and its maker</i>

01:39:59.445 --> 01:40:02.937
<i>have challenged my preconceptions</i>
<i>about fine cooking</i>

01:40:03.048 --> 01:40:05.744
